- "captains of sinking ships" refers to individuals or organizations with high-risk scores and high spending;
- "at high risk" refers to risk scores greater than 0.5 and probabilities greater than 0.7;
- "risk threshold greater than 0.9" indicates a very high risk level;
- "alert type 'high risk'" specifies the type of alert being considered.

